The root rot causing fungal pathogen, 
 Fusarium solani Fs4 (Accession: JN232142.1) was previously isolated from common bean roots exhibiting typical symptoms of root rots as described by 
 Abawi and Pastor Corrales (1990). Isolation material was collected in a commercial farm devastated by the disease, and the fungus was isolated (
 Al-Askar and Rashad, 2010). Information's pertaining to its identity and virulence toward common bean seedlings are extensively documented (
 Nana et al., 2015b; 
 Toghueo et al., 2016; 
 Eke et al., 2016; 
 Eke et al., 2016, 
 2016, 
 2019).
